June 9 (Reuters) -  U.S. stock index futures pointed to modest losses at the open on Monday, as a rash of corporate deals weren't enough reason for investors to keep buying following a rally that has taken major indexes to repeated record highs. Dow Jones industrial average futures <1YMc1> were down 0.09 percent at 16,916, S&P 500 futures <ESc1> were down 0.13 percent at 1,946.75 and Nasdaq 100 futures <NQc1> were down 0.09 percent at 3,794.75. [.N]

** UNION PACIFIC CORP <UNP.N>, Friday close $201.86, -49.52 pct premarket A two-for-one split of the largest U.S. railroad company's  stock was enforced on Monday. The company, on May 15, said its board had authorized the stock split with the stock dividend paid on June 6. [ID:nPn1ClH7X]  ** MERCK & CO INC <MRK.N>, Friday close $57.85, -0.66 pct premarket ** IDENIX PHARMACEUTICALS INC <IDIX.O>, Friday close $7.23, +231.67 pct premarket ** ACHILLION PHARMACEUTICALS INC <ACHN.O>, Friday close $2.88, +42.36 pct premarket Merck & Co said it would buy Idenix Pharmaceuticals in a deal valued at about $3.85 billion to complement its hepatitis C portfolio. [ID:nL4N0OQ2Y3] Shares of Achillion Pharmaceuticals, another maker of hepatitis C drugs, also rose on the news.   ** APPLE INC <AAPL.O>, Friday close $645.57, -85.73 pct premarket A seven-for-one split of the iPad maker's stock, announced in April, was enforced on Monday. Apple was the fourth S&P company to announce a stock split this year. [ID:nL2N0NG1CU].  ** ANALOG DEVICES INC <ADI.O>, Friday close $52.69, +4.65 pct premarket ** HITTITE MICROWAVE CORP <HITT.O>, Friday close $60.56, +28.55 pct premarket Chipmaker Analog Devices said it would buy Hittite Microwave in a deal valued at $2 billion to strengthen its radio frequency (RF) and signal conversion chip offerings. [ID:nL4N0OQ2T4]  ** MCDONALD'S CORP <MCD.N>, Friday close $101.96 McDonald's reported better-than-expected global sales at established restaurants in May, helped by strong demand in China, but sales in the United States continued to fall.. [ID:nL4N0OQ32E]  ** NEUSTAR INC <NSR.N>, Friday close $26.67, -8.10 pct premarket Neustar could lose a phone contract to rival Ericsson <ERICb.ST>, media reports said citing an e-mail made public on a government website. The company routes phone calls and manages databases used by North American telecom carriers. (http://link.reuters.com/byz89v)  ** FAMILY DOLLAR STORES INC <FDO.N>, Friday close $60.53, +12.34 pct prema